# Authentication Memory
# Loaded when: auth, jwt, oauth, tokens, login, sessions mentioned

@meta: keywords=auth,jwt,oauth,tokens,sessions | priority=high | updated=2026-03-05

## IMPLEMENTATION
jwt:
  lib: jsonwebtoken@9.x
  secret: process.env.JWT_SECRET (256-bit)
  algorithm: HS256
  tokens:
    access: expiry:15m | payload:{userId,role,email}
    refresh: expiry:7d | stored:redis | rotation:yes
  location: src/auth/jwt.ts

oauth:
  providers: Google,GitHub
  strategy: passport.js
  callback: /auth/callback/:provider
  scopes: Google[email,profile] | GitHub[user:email]
  config: src/auth/oauth/*.ts

sessions:
  storage: Redis
  key: session:{userId}
  ttl: 7d
  data: {userId,role,lastActive,deviceInfo}

## MIDDLEWARE
auth: src/middleware/auth.ts | validates JWT | attaches req.user
optional-auth: src/middleware/optionalAuth.ts | doesn't fail if no token
role-guard: src/middleware/roleGuard.ts | requires(role:admin|moderator)

## ENDPOINTS
POST /auth/register | body:{email,password,name} | returns:{user,tokens}
POST /auth/login | body:{email,password} | returns:{tokens}
POST /auth/refresh | body:{refreshToken} | returns:{accessToken}
POST /auth/logout | header:Authorization | clears refresh token
GET /auth/me | header:Authorization | returns:User

GET /auth/oauth/:provider | redirects to OAuth provider
GET /auth/callback/:provider | OAuth callback | returns:{user,tokens}

## SECURITY
- Passwords: bcrypt | rounds:12 | src/utils/password.ts
- Rate limiting: 5 attempts/15min per IP on login
- Refresh rotation: old refresh token invalidated on use
- Token blacklist: Redis set for logged-out tokens
- CSRF protection: double-submit cookie pattern

## FLOWS
# Registration
1. Validate input (Zod)
2. Check email uniqueness
3. Hash password (bcrypt)
4. Create user in DB
5. Generate JWT pair
6. Store refresh token in Redis
7. Return tokens

# OAuth
1. Redirect to provider
2. User authorizes
3. Callback with code
4. Exchange code for profile
5. Find or create user
6. Generate JWT pair
7. Return tokens

## ERRORS
InvalidCredentials | 401 | wrong email/password
TokenExpired | 401 | JWT expired
InvalidToken | 401 | JWT malformed/invalid
EmailTaken | 409 | email already registered
UnauthorizedError | 403 | valid token but insufficient permissions

